## API Reference

### IVectorStore Interface

All implementations provide:

```typescript
interface IVectorStore {
  // Insert or update documents
  upsert(documents: VectorDocument[]): Promise<void>;

  // Search by embedding vector
  search(query: number[], options?: VectorSearchOptions): Promise<VectorSearchResult[]>;

  // Search by text (auto-generates embedding)
  searchByText(text: string, options?: VectorSearchOptions): Promise<VectorSearchResult[]>;

  // Delete by IDs
  delete(ids: string[]): Promise<void>;

  // Delete by metadata filter
  deleteByFilter(filter: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<number>;

  // Get single document
  get(id: string): Promise<VectorDocument | null>;

  // Get multiple documents
  getMany(ids: string[]): Promise<VectorDocument[]>;

  // Count documents
  count(filter?: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<number>;
}
```

### Types

```typescript
interface VectorDocument {
  id: string;
  content: string;
  embedding?: number[];
  metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
}

interface VectorSearchResult {
  id: string;
  content: string;
  score: number;
  metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
}

interface VectorSearchOptions {
  topK?: number;           // Default: 10
  threshold?: number;      // Default: 0.0 (0-1 range)
  filter?: Record<string, unknown>;
  includeVectors?: boolean; // Default: false
}
```

## Performance Tips

### Batch Operations

```typescript
// ❌ Slow: Individual upserts
for (const doc of documents) {
  await store.upsert([doc]);
}

// ✅ Fast: Batch upsert
await store.upsert(documents);
```

### Pre-Compute Embeddings

```typescript
// ❌ Slower: Generate embeddings one-by-one
for (const doc of docs) {
  await store.upsert([{ ...doc }]); // Generates embedding per doc
}

// ✅ Faster: Batch generate embeddings
const embeddings = await generateEmbeddings(docs.map((d) => d.content));
await store.upsert(docs.map((doc, i) => ({ ...doc, embedding: embeddings[i] })));
```

### Use Appropriate topK

```typescript
// Only retrieve what you need
const results = await store.searchByText(query, {
  topK: 5, // Don't fetch 100 if you only need 5
});
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
import { VectorStoreError, ConnectionError } from '@/integrations/ai/vectordb';

try {
  await store.upsert(documents);
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof ConnectionError) {
    console.error('Database connection failed:', error.message);
  } else if (error instanceof VectorStoreError) {
    console.error('Vector store error:', error.code, error.details);
  } else {
    console.error('Unexpected error:', error);
  }
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Use Metadata Filters**: Add rich metadata for better filtering
2. **Chunk Strategically**: Use appropriate chunk sizes (500-1500 chars)
3. **Set Thresholds**: Filter low-quality results with similarity threshold
4. **Batch Operations**: Process documents in batches for efficiency
5. **Monitor Costs**: Track embedding API usage and vector DB operations
6. **Multi-Tenancy**: Use namespaces (Pinecone) or metadata filters (others)

## Troubleshooting

### Connection Issues

```typescript
// Check connection
try {
  const count = await store.count();
  console.log('Connected! Documents:', count);
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Connection failed:', error);
}
```

### Embedding Dimension Mismatch

```typescript
// Ensure dimension matches your embedding model
const config = getEmbeddingConfig();
console.log('Embedding dimensions:', config.dimensions);

// Create store with matching dimension
const store = createVectorStore({
  indexName: 'my-index',
  dimension: config.dimensions, // Must match!
});
```

### No Results Found

```typescript
// Lower threshold if getting no results
const results = await store.searchByText(query, {
  topK: 10,
  threshold: 0.5, // Try lowering from 0.7 to 0.5
});

// Check document count
const total = await store.count();
console.log('Total documents:', total);
```

## Migration Guide

### From pgvector to Pinecone/Qdrant/Weaviate

```typescript
// 1. Export from pgvector
import { searchVectors } from '@/integrations/ai/rag/vector-store';
const oldDocs = await searchVectors({ embedding: dummyVector, limit: 10000 });

// 2. Import to new provider
import { createVectorStore } from '@/integrations/ai/vectordb';
const newStore = createVectorStore({ indexName: 'migrated', dimension: 1536 });

await newStore.upsert(
  oldDocs.map((doc) => ({
    id: doc.id,
    content: doc.content,
    embedding: doc.embedding,
    metadata: doc.metadata,
  }))
);
```

